This property is calculated from WaitTimeCategory property: -1 equals to Unknown, 0-5 equals to Normal and 6-10 equals to Critical Access control everyone WaitTimeCategory Type: System.Int32 Type of the "Wait" meter. Contains numeric values -1..10, meaning DOWN(-1), IDLE(0), LOW(1), ..., HIGH(5), LOW_ABNORMAL(6), ..., HIGH_ABNORMAL(10). In DPA UI, values 1-5 are shown as blue meter, abnormal values 6-10 have red meter. Normal/abnormal is an intra-instance information, indicating whether wait time of this particular instance is higher than usual for this instance, based on historical data. Values LOW - HIGH (normal as well as abnormal) represent inter-instance comparison, ie. how big/significant is today's wait time of this particular instance when compared to today's wait times of the other monitored instances. Access control everyone WaitTimeSecs Type: System.Double Total wait time today in seconds (in DPA, shows when you hover over the "Wait" meter). schema/DPA.TrendDataDimension.html.keywords: DPA.TrendDataDimension SolarWinds Information Service 2019.2.5200 Schema Documentation Trend data for DB instance per dimension Inheritance ↳ System.Entity ↳ System.ExtensionEntity Access control Operations Right read everyone Properties DatabaseId Type: System.Int32 Reference to Orion.DPA.DatabaseInstance.Id. This parameter is not required for data-dimensions 18, 19 and 20 (see bellow – virtual dimensions). On the other hand this parameter can be specified with WHERE Id IN (x, y, z) for these three dimensions Access control everyone GlobalDatabaseId Type: System.Int32 Unique ID of database instance in Orion Access control everyone Id Type: System.Int32 Trend data-dimension; possible values are: SQL (1), WAIT (2), PROGRAM (3), DATABASE_INSTANCE (4), MACHINE (5), DB_USER (6), OS_USER (7), FILE (8), DRIVE (9), PLAN (10), ACTION (11), MODULE (12), PARTITION (13), OBJECT (14), PROCEDURE (15) and virtual dimensions TOP_WAIT (18), TRENDING_UP_WAIT (19), TRENDING_DOWN_WAIT (20) Access control everyone Name Type: System.String Data-dimension names–readable data-dimension representations: 'SQL Statement', 'Wait-time', 'Program', 'Database', 'Machine', 'Database User', 'O/S User', 'File', 'Drive', 'Plan', 'Action', 'Module', 'Partition', 'Object', 'Procedure', 'Top Wait-time', 'Trending-up Wait-time', 'Trending-down Wait-time' Access control everyone Wait Type: System.Double Total wait-time in seconds for each returned record. For Trending-up (down) wait-time this value represents percent change (not time) Access control everyone AverageWait Type: System.Double Average wait-time in seconds for DB instance Access control everyone Time Type: System.DateTime Time-stamp of entity record (operators <, <=, > and >= can be used in WHERE clauses on this field) Access control everyone TimeUnit Type: System.Int32 Used for filtration of records by setting desired granularity (millis (0), seconds (1), minutes (2), hours (3), days (4), weeks (5), months (6)) Since this is only a prototype the only values allowed are 3 (hours) and 4 (days) and both are mutually exclusive (you cannot get records for both hours and days by a single query) Access control everyone InstanceId Type: System.Int64 IDs of an instances in DPA; for programs, machines, users, etc. these are typically generically-generated IDs in local repository table; for SQL texts these are SQL hashes Access control everyone InstanceName Type: System.String Name of an instance; e.g. 'IGNITE' (for program), 'administrator-XYZ' (for user), 348A3F21 (for SQL text) Access control everyone InstanceValue Type: System.String Typically set only for SQLs–this field contains full SQL text Access control everyone MaxInstances Type: System.Int32 Serves only to limit the maximal number of monitored database instances to be retrieved (top 5, 10, etc.) Access control everyone DisplayName Type: System.String Access control everyone Description Type: System.String Access control everyone InstanceType Type: System.Type Access control everyone Uri Type: System.String Access control everyone InstanceSiteId Type: System.Int32 Access control everyone

schema/DPA.ResourceDefinition.html.keywords: DPA.ResourceDefinition SolarWinds Information Service 2019.2.5200 Schema Documentation Provides definition of DB resources (metrics grouped in categories). It provides no dynamic values (in terms values don't change in time unless user takes actions which will cause definition change) and as such it requires no time-frame. Inheritance ↳ System.Entity ↳ System.ExtensionEntity Access control Operations Right read everyone Properties Name Type: System.String Specifies a name of a resource (e.g. Active Sessions, Memory Utilization, Signal Waits Percent) Access control everyone DisplayName Type: System.String Resource name used in DPA UI Access control everyone CategoryName Type: System.String Specifies a name of a category a resource belongs (e.g. CPU, Memory, Sessions) Access control everyone Description Type: System.String Specifies a short description of a resource (e.g. Number of batches being executed by SQL Server every second for resource having name Batch Requests Per Sec and belonging to category Sessions) Access control everyone ValueUnit Type: System.String Specifies a unit of this metric (e.g. requests/second, %, pages/second). Unit is represented on Y axis of resource graph. Access control everyone Thresholds Type: System.String Specifies a comma separated list of threshold values. It contains both WARN and CRITICAL limits where first two values are WARN limits and second two CRITICAL limits (e.g. 80,90,90,null) Access control everyone DatabaseId Type: System.Int32 Specifies for which DB instance is this resource applicable. Reference to Orion.DPA.DatabaseInstance.Id Access control everyone GlobalDatabaseId Type: System.Int32 Unique ID of database instance in Orion Access control everyone DisplayName Type: System.String Access control everyone Description Type: System.String Access control everyone InstanceType Type: System.Type Access control everyone Uri Type: System.String Access control everyone InstanceSiteId Type: System.Int32 Access control everyone

schema/DPA.ResourceData.html.title: DPA.ResourceData | Orion SDK Schemas
schema/DPA.ResourceData.html.keywords: DPA.ResourceData SolarWinds Information Service 2019.2.5200 Schema Documentation Provides data-points of DB resources. It has single parameter that is required (DatabaseId) and two more that specifies what data will be returned for a given query. If one specifies both ResourceName and CategoryName in a WHERE clause than result set will contain single-resource data-points for specified time-frame (or default time-frame if Time property was not limited in WHERE clause). If at least one of these two parameters is missing than the result set will contain multiple-metric data-points limited by one data-point per metric (i.e. result set will contain a set of last data-point collected for each metric, if such data-point exists in last 60 minutes) Inheritance ↳ System.Entity ↳ System.ExtensionEntity Access control Operations Right read everyone Properties DatabaseId Type: System.Int32 Specifies for which DB instance should resource data-points be fetched. Reference to Orion.DPA.DatabaseInstance.Id Access control everyone GlobalDatabaseId Type: System.Int32 Unique ID of database instance in Orion Access control everyone ResourceName Type: System.String Specifies a name of a resource (e.g. Active Sessions, Memory Utilization, Signal Waits Percent) that must be equal to one of the records from DPA.ResourceDefinition.Name Access control everyone CategoryName Type: System.String Specifies a name of a category a resource belongs (e.g. CPU, Memory, Sessions) that must be equal to one of the records from DPA.ResourceDefinition.CategoryName Access control everyone Time Type: System.DateTime Specifies a time of a data-point Access control everyone Value Type: System.Double Specifies a double-precision value of this data-point in given time Access control everyone TimeUnit Type: System.Int32 Specifies a time-frame for which data-points should be fetched. If both Time > ABC and Time < XYZ are specified in WHERE clause this property will be ignored. It can take one of the following values: hour (3), day (4), week (5), month (6), six moths (61) or year (7). If Time is limited only by one side (< or >) than a time-frame will be specified as Time-TimeUnit to Time respectively Time to Time+TimeUnit Access control everyone TimesliceUnit Type: System.Int32 Force granularity of records within Time interval (by default there is auto detection based on the Time interval), supported values: as collected ('-1'), ten minutes (22), hour (3), day (4) Access control everyone DisplayName Type: System.String Access control everyone Description Type: System.String Access control everyone InstanceType Type: System.Type Access control everyone Uri Type: System.String Access control everyone InstanceSiteId Type: System.Int32 Access control everyone

'CPU/Memory') Access control everyone AdviceInfo Type: System.String HTML-formatted text describing the wait time, causes, possible fixes etc. Access control everyone DisplayName Type: System.String Access control everyone Description Type: System.String Access control everyone InstanceType Type: System.Type Access control everyone Uri Type: System.String Access control everyone InstanceSiteId Type: System.Int32 Access control everyone

schema/DPA.DetailDataDimension.html.title: DPA.DetailDataDimension | Orion SDK Schemas
schema/DPA.DetailDataDimension.html.keywords: DPA.DetailDataDimension SolarWinds Information Service 2019.2.5200 Schema Documentation Detail Wait Time statistics for DB instance Inheritance ↳ System.Entity ↳ System.ExtensionEntity Access control Operations Right read everyone Properties DatabaseId Type: System.Int32 Reference to Orion.DPA.DatabaseInstance.Id Access control everyone GlobalDatabaseId Type: System.Int32 Unique ID of database instance in Orion Access control everyone DimensionId Type: System.Int32 Detail data-dimension; possible values are: SQL (1), WAIT (2), PROGRAM (3), DATABASE_INSTANCE (4), MACHINE (5), DB_USER (6), OS_USER (7), FILE (8), DRIVE (9), PLAN (10), ACTION (11), MODULE (12), PARTITION (13), OBJECT (14), PROCEDURE (15), SESSION (16) Access control everyone InstanceId Type: System.String IDs of an instances in DPA; for programs, machines, users, etc. these are typically generically-generated IDs in local repository table; for SQL texts these are SQL hashes Access control everyone InstanceName Type: System.String Name of an instance; e.g. 'IGNITE' (for program), 'administrator-XYZ' (for user), 348A3F21 (for SQL text) Access control everyone TopN Type: System.Int32 Limits the maximal number of categories (SQLs, programs etc.) to be retrieved for the specified time interval. Ignored for WAIT dimension if the TimesliceUnit is not provided. If TopN is not specified, default value is the NUMBER_OF_ITEMS_IN_TIMESERIES_CHART attribute in DPA config for the given monitored database instance. Access control everyone InstanceValue Type: System.String For SQL time-slice – this field contains full SQL text; For other time-slice dimensions it is empty; For all non time-slice dimensions it contains WAIT cause Access control everyone IntervalUnit Type: System.Int32 Allowed values are HOUR (3), TWO_HOURS (30), THREE_HOURS (31), FOUR_HOURS (32), SIX_HOURS (33), EIGHT_HOURS (34), TWELVE_HOURS (35 Access control everyone Time Type: System.DateTime Time-stamp of entity record (operators <, <=, > and >= can be used in WHERE clauses on this field) Access control everyone TimesliceUnit Type: System.Int32 Specifies how time-frame should be split. Allowed values are (other than ones in IntervalUnit) FIVE_SECONDS (10), TEN_SECONDS (11), FIFTEEN_SECONDS (12), TWENTY_SECONDS (13), THIRTY_SECONDS (14), MINUTE (2), TWO_MINUTES (20), FIVE_MINUTES (21), TEN_MINUTES (22), TWENTY_MINUTES (23), THIRTY_MINUTES (24), TWO_DAYS (40), THREE_DAYS (41) Access control everyone Wait Type: System.Double Total wait-time in seconds for each returned record Access control everyone Executions Type: System.Int32 Number of Executions for each returned value. Returns 'null' if value is not specified (e.g. Timeslice < 10 min or Dimension <> 1 ), -1 if 'Not Available' (e.g. in Truncate queries), otherwise not negative number Access control everyone Average Type: System.Double Average in seconds for each returned value. Returns 'null' if value is not specified (e.g. Timeslice < 10 min or Dimension <> 1 ), -1 if 'Not Available' (e.g. in Truncate queries), otherwise not negative number Access control everyone MachineIdentifier Type: System.String Machine identifier Access control everyone AdditionalValue Type: System.String Access control everyone DisplayName Type: System.String Access control everyone Description Type: System.String Access control everyone InstanceType Type: System.Type Access control everyone Uri Type: System.String Access control everyone InstanceSiteId Type: System.Int32 Access control everyone

Parameters Name Description limitationTypeID required. LimitationTypeID from Orion.LimitationTypes. selection required if Limitation is of type "Selection" as defined in Orion.LimitationTypes. A string that will be used to match one value against the Table & Field defined by corresponding Orion.LimitationType. checkboxItems required if Limitation is of type "Checkbox" as defined in Orion.LimitationTypes. An array of strings used to match multiple values against the Table & Field defined by corresponding Orion.LimitationType. pattern required if Limitation is of type "Pattern" as defined in Orion.LimitationTypes. A string that will be used to match multiple values as a text search pattern against the Table & Field defined by corresponding Orion.LimitationType. accountID optional. Account ID as defined in Orion.Accounts. Recommended to always specify this parameter. Advanced usage: omit this parameter to create an un-assigned Limitation, as such it will only be used if explicitly specified using "WITH LIMITATION ID" SWQL expression. Returns ID of the newly created Orion.Limitation instance. Access control Operations Right invoke admin UpdateLimitation Updates Limitation to a new definition i.e. new set of items it shoud match. Parameters Name Description limitationID required. Limitation ID from Orion.Limitations. selection required if Limitation is of type "Selection" as defined in Orion.LimitationTypes. A string that will be used to match one value against the Table & Field defined by corresponding Orion.LimitationType. checkboxItems required if Limitation is of type "Checkbox" as defined in Orion.LimitationTypes. An array of strings used to match multiple values against the Table & Field defined by corresponding Orion.LimitationType. pattern required if Limitation is of type "Pattern" as defined in Orion.LimitationTypes. A string that will be used to match multiple values as a text search pattern against the Table & Field defined by corresponding Orion.LimitationType. Access control Operations Right invoke admin DeleteLimitation Deletes Limitation and removes it from an Account it was assigned to previously. Parameters Name Description limitationID required. Limitation ID from Orion.Limitations. Access control Operations Right invoke admin

schema/Orion.HA.Pools.html.title: Orion.HA.Pools | Orion SDK Schemas
schema/Orion.HA.Pools.html.keywords: Orion.HA.Pools SolarWinds Information Service 2019.2.5200 Schema Documentation High Availability pools. Pool unites pool members of the same type to provide high availability of Orion servers. Inheritance ↳ System.Entity Access control Operations Right read everyone create,read,update,delete,invoke admin Properties PoolId Type: System.Int32 ID of pool Access control everyone PoolMasterMemberId Type: System.Int32 ID of pool member which acts as a pool master Access control everyone PoolType Type: System.String Type of pool (0 - main poller, 1 - additional poller) Access control everyone DisplayName Type: System.String Name of a pool Access control everyone Enabled Type: System.Boolean Pool is enabled or disabled Access control everyone CurrentStatus Type: System.Int32 Current status of a pool Access control everyone CurrentStatusTimestamp Type: System.DateTime Timestamp of current status Access control everyone PoolMasterChangeTimestamp Type: System.DateTime Timestamp of pool master role change Access control everyone IntervalMemberDown Type: System.Int32 Interval after which is member considered as down Access control everyone IntervalPoolTask Type: System.Int32 Pool task interval in seconds. In this interval HA service performs regular tasks e.g. services status monitoring Access control everyone IntervalSuicideRule Type: System.Int32 Interval after which member releases its resource if it cannot reach other member of a pool do database Access control everyone VirtualHostName Type: System.String Virtual Host name assigned to a pool Access control everyone VirtualIpAddress Type: System.String Virtual IP Address assigned to a pool Access control everyone DnsIpAddress Type: System.String IP Address of DNS server hosting primary zone used by virtual host name Access control everyone DnsZone Type: System.String A name of forward lookup DNS zone where virtual host name record is stored Access control everyone DnsType Type: System.String Type of DNS server (Microsoft, BIND, Other) Access control everyone DisplayName Type: System.String Access control everyone Description Type: System.String Access control everyone InstanceType Type: System.Type Access control everyone Uri Type: System.String Access control everyone InstanceSiteId Type: System.Int32 Access control everyone Verbs CreatePool Creates pool based on provided members and resource parameters Parameters Name Description displayName Name of a pool poolMembersIds Integer array of pool member IDs properties Additional properties containing resources configurations. Returns Object which describes, whether pool was created. Property Code = 0 means that operation was successful. Property Result contains ID of created pool. Property Message contains error message in case of error. Access control Operations Right invoke admin EditPool Updates pool with a given poolId Parameters Name Description poolId Pool ID displayName Name of a pool properties Additional properties containing resources configurations. Returns Object which describes, whether pool was edited. Property Code = 0 means that operation was successful. Property Message contains error message in case of error. Access control Operations Right invoke admin ValidateCreatePool Validates pool (without creating it) based on provided members and resource parameters Parameters Name Description displayName Name of a pool poolMembersIds Integer array of pool member IDs properties Additional properties containing resources configurations. Returns Object which contains validation result. Property Code = 0 means that validation was successful. Property Result contains validation result data. Property Message contains error message in case of error. Access control Operations Right invoke admin ValidateEditPool Validates pool with given poolId and resource parameters (without actual update) Parameters Name Description poolId Pool ID displayName Name of a pool properties Additional properties containing resources configurations. Returns Object which contains validation result. Property Code = 0 means that validation was successful. Property Result contains validation result data. Property Message contains error message in case of error. Access control Operations Right invoke admin EnablePool Enables pool with a given poolId Parameters Name Description poolId ID of pool Returns Object which describes, whether pool was enabled. Property Code = 0 means that operation was successful. Property Message contains error message in case of error. Access control Operations Right invoke admin DisablePool Disables pool with a given poolId Parameters Name Description poolId ID of pool Returns Object which describes, whether pool was disabled. Property Code = 0 means that operation was successful. Property Message contains error message in case of error. Access control Operations Right invoke admin DeletePool Delete pool with given poolId. Parameters Name Description poolId ID of pool Returns Object which describes, whether pool was deleted. Property Code = 0 means that operation was successful. Property Message contains error message in case of error. Access control Operations Right invoke admin Switchover Manual failover on a given pool. Parameters Name Description poolId ID of pool Returns Object which describes, whether manual failover was initiated. Property Code = 0 means that operation was successful. Property Message contains error message in case of error. Access control Operations Right invoke admin DeleteStaleEngine Deletes OrionServer and related pool memeber with a given hostName. Parameters Name Description hostName hostName Returns Object which describes, whether stale engine was deleted. Property Code = 0 means that operation was successful. Property Message contains error message in case of error. Access control Operations Right invoke admin
